description.p:
i) the carbonaceous residue levels are very low, less than 2% by weight, after the frit is subjected to the appropriate heating cycle;


ii) contamination from water which is known to give rise to Theological instability in the case of conventional nitrocellulose/ester systems is not an issue with the present invention;


iii) the sealing glass pastes do not contain volatile organic solvents and thus there are no problems with VOC emissions;


iv) the sealing glass pastes of the present invention produce seals which are resistant to high voltage breakdown and hermetic failure.
